  "text": "The rat NP cells were isolated, as described previously [CITATION_1] . The NP cells were seeded into 60 mm tissue culture dishes and grown in complete culture medium at 37˚C with 5% CO 2 . The culture medium was replaced every 2-3 days. The cells were passaged by digestion with 0.25% trypsin (Gibco Life Technologies) once they reached 80-90% confluence. The NP cells at passage 3 in culture medium were used for subsequent experiments.",
